    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-5">Data visualization</h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Visualizations allow us to get a quick overview of the data to better understand the type of data we will be working with. This is often one of the first steps in working with data.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">There are many ways to visualize data:</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><ul><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Scatter plots: </strong>they are great for determining whether there is a relationship between two quantitative variables, and if so, of what type.</li><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Bar charts: </strong>they are especially useful to represent the relationship between a categorical and a numerical variable</li><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Histograms: </strong>they help us represent the distribution of numerical data</li><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;"><strong>Pie Charts: </strong>they can be used to represent numerical proportions</li></ul></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
