750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/1*zgUMHUCemdeU256B3grKxw.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/1*zgUMHUCemdeU256B3grKxw.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/1*zgUMHUCemdeU256B3grKxw.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*zgUMHUCemdeU256B3grKxw.png 1400w"/><img alt="" loading="lazy" role="presentation" src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:700/1*zgUMHUCemdeU256B3grKxw.png"></picture></div><p class="mbr-description mbr-fonts-style mt-2 align-center display-12 text-muted" style="font-size:12px;">Distribution of House sale prices, showing the central tendencies and the skewness of the data</p><br></div></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-7">Skewness</h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">When most values are on the left side of the distribution, as in the figure above, we say that the data is <strong>skewed to the right, </strong>as the right tail is longer. For unimodal distributions, this often means a <strong>positive skewness.</strong></p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Moreover, most of the time, in these situations we find that:</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
