    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Furthermore, the shape of the bell curve depends on the standard deviation.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><ul><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">If the <strong>standard deviation is low</strong>, it means that the data is not very spread out, and therefore we will have a <strong>narrower, taller curve</strong></li><li class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">If the <strong>standard deviation is high</strong>, it means that on average, the observations are farther from the mean, resulting in a <strong>wider, flatter curve</strong></li></ul></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
